Based on physical evidence _ including a rifle e5:found in April month e6:buried near the doctor's house and a e8:match between fibers e7:found near the murder and others e9:found in Kopp's car _ officials e10:said they had e11:decided to e12:issue a warrant for his arrest in the e13:killing of Dr. Barnett Slepian.

In desperate need of hard currency, Castro e74:relaxed travel restrictions and e75:allowed Cubans to have U.S. dollars, e76:triggering a trickle of cash from Miami that soon e78:became a flood.

The tourism industry in Kenya has been troubled for years _ in part because of the e114:opening of new safari destinations in South Africa, in part because of Nairobi's well-deserved reputation for street crime. Tourism industry revenues reportedly e50:dropped to $300 million last year, down from $450 million the year before.
The government has e51:responded to the slump with a series of e118:actions to e140:lure tourists back, including a marked improvement in the service of Kenya Airways, the national airline, which has e54:gone into partnership with KLM Royal Dutch Airlines. The e120:bombing will doubtless e55:set back those efforts.

But the lack of infrastructure has e57:worked to Tanzania's advantage in recent years given the dramatic growth in the number of adventure travelers who are willing, even eager to e59:go without the five-star safari resorts that Kenya offers. The U.S. Immigration and Naturalization Service e2:made a reasonable e47:decision Wednesday in e48:ruling that Elian Gonzalez, the 6-year-old boy who e3:survived an ill-fated migrant smuggling e50:trip across the Florida Straits, should be e72:reunited with his father back in Cuba. The e51:decision will e5:inflame anti-Castro Cubans in Miami, but Doris Meissner, the INS commissioner, e6:made it clear that the service had e7:followed established policy in the case. Moreover, by e9:setting a Jan. 14 e52:return date, the immigration service e10:allowed Elian's American relatives time to e11:test the e54:ruling in court.
Elian was one of 13 Cubans who were e12:trying to e13:cross from Cuba to Florida six weeks ago on a 17-foot aluminum powerboat when it e14:capsized.
